The debt limit is the only leverage we have against big spenders in both parties to reduce the size, scope, and cost of government and stop mortgaging our children’s future.  

We need to convince President Trump to embrace that leverage and use his negotiating skills to do just that.  

@elonmusk @VivekGRamaswamy

The uniparty has deviously converted discretionary into mandatory spending – enabling them to spend a lot more.

My chart shows Other Mandatory Spending (OMS) has increased $681B since FY2019 – almost as much as Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid combined.

@DOGE should seriously look at the $1.3T in OSM for signification savings.

